  "market_context": "EURUSD 5-minute chart on 22/12/2023 around 07:00–08:00 UTC-5, price had rallied forming a high, pulled back to a low, then pushed to a higher high near 1.1034 before reversing and forming a lower low, completing a bearish breaker structure.",
  "key_observation": "The sequence high → low → higher high → lower low formed a valid bearish breaker. The series of down-close candles between the low and higher high becomes the breaker zone, and a bearish fair value gap overlaps it, creating a Unicorn model.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that the prior structure did not form a lower low initially, so no breaker yet existed.",
    "Step 2: Re-examine and identify the bearish breaker sequence: high, low, higher high, then a lower low confirming the pattern.",
    "Step 3: Mark out the series of down-close candles between the low and the higher high as the bearish breaker block zone.",
    "Step 4: Anticipate price retracing back up to retest the breaker block and then deliver displacement lower.",
    "Step 5: Confirm displacement created a bearish fair value gap overlapping the breaker, forming the Unicorn model.",
    "Step 6: Define entry options — either at the start of the fair value gap, or at the breaker within the fair value gap.",
    "Step 7: Define stop placement options — above the swing high or just above the breaker block, targeting 2R."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price retested the bearish breaker, displaced lower, and reached 2R quickly when stop was placed above the breaker block. Using the swing high as stop would have just missed take-profit and stopped out.",
  "lessons": "A valid bearish breaker requires the high–low–higher high–lower low sequence, and is strongest when paired with displacement creating an overlapping fair value gap (Unicorn model). Stop placement choice (swing high vs. breaker top) materially affects trade outcome.",
